## Working rules

Do not write production code unless the relevant product decision or discovery note exists.

Do not turn DailyPaws into a generic obedience, trick or habit-tracking app.

When uncertain, protect the product philosophy.

# Working Agreement

This repository follows a documentation-first approach.

Before implementing features, understand the product.

## Documentation hierarchy

If two documents conflict, the following order applies:

1. ProductBible.md
2. ProductDecisions.md
3. ProductModel.md
4. Discovery.md

## Session workflow

Every session should:

1. Focus on one concept.
2. End with a documented decision.
3. Update the relevant documentation.
4. Move unresolved ideas to Questions.md or the Parking Lot.

## Working principles

- One session = one decision.
- Documentation before implementation.
- Build only from approved documentation.
- New ideas go to the Parking Lot.
- Avoid creating new documents unless absolutely necessary.

